🧠 Assignment Prompt: Fitness Center Management System

You are designing a small object-oriented system for a fitness center.

Part 1 — Create an Interface

Create an interface called:

Trackable


It must declare:

double calculateWeeklyCaloriesBurned();

void displayActivityInfo();

Any class that implements this interface must define how it:

Calculates calories burned per week

Displays its activity information

Part 2 — Create an Abstract Class

Create an abstract class called:

Member


It must include:

Fields (protected):

String name

int age

double weight

Constructor:

Initialize all fields

Concrete Method:

void checkIn() → prints something like:
"Member <name> has checked in."

Abstract Method:

String getMembershipType();

Part 3 — Create Concrete Classes

Create at least two subclasses that:

Extend Member

Implement Trackable

Examples:

WeightLifter

Runner

Swimmer

Each subclass must:

Provide its own implementation of:

calculateWeeklyCaloriesBurned()

displayActivityInfo()

getMembershipType()

Each activity should calculate calories differently.

Part 4 — Driver Class

In main():

Create at least two different member objects

Store them in a collection (ArrayList)

Loop through them and:

Call checkIn()

Display membership type

Call displayActivityInfo()

Print weekly calories burned

🎯 Design Requirements

You must demonstrate:

Polymorphism (store them as Member or Trackable)

Proper method overriding

Clear separation of:

Shared state → abstract class

Shared capability → interface

🚫 Constraints

Do NOT use static methods for behavior

Do NOT put everything in one class

Do NOT hardcode everything in main()